HEADWORD: Chelonia
<hw>Che*lo"ni*a</hw> <pr>(k⟦esl⟧*l⟦omac⟧"n⟦icr⟧*⟦adot⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>chelw`nh</grk> a
tortoise.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An order of reptiles, including
the tortoises and turtles, peculiar in having a part of the vertebr⟦ae⟧,
ribs, and sternum united with the dermal plates so as to form a firm
shell. The jaws are covered by a horny beak. See <er>Reptilia</er>;
also, <xex>Illust.</xex> in Appendix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chelonian</ent>⟦br⟧
